1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:01,960
[thunder rumbling]

2
00:00:02,043 --> 00:00:03,002
[Marcus] <i>My brother died,</i>

3
00:00:03,086 --> 00:00:05,463
<i>and my family was torn apart</i>
<i>because of what happened.</i>

4
00:00:05,547 --> 00:00:07,924
[Datu Rahman] <i>I wasn't the one</i>
<i>who blew up that ship.</i>

5
00:00:08,008 --> 00:00:11,386
I was there because I was trying
to stop the explosion.

6
00:00:11,469 --> 00:00:14,014
- [tense music playing]
- I was with my friend, Victor.

7
00:00:14,097 --> 00:00:15,390
[Datu Rahman] Victor Reyes.

8
00:00:15,473 --> 00:00:17,976
I only found out recently
that he was your father.

9
00:00:18,059 --> 00:00:21,563
[Jalil] <i>The day after tomorrow,</i>
<i>they'll find out that I'm Jalil Abubakar.</i>

10
00:00:21,646 --> 00:00:23,440
<i>Marcus will get dragged into this.</i>

11
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:25,150
<i>Doctor Teresa and Marcus are safer</i>

12
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:27,610
<i>if they know nothing</i>
<i>about who I really am.</i>

13
00:00:27,694 --> 00:00:30,155
They can't be connected to me.

14
00:00:30,238 --> 00:00:31,114
[knocking on door]

15
00:00:32,574 --> 00:00:35,035
[suspenseful music playing]

16
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:37,954
[Dante] <i>Manuel was the one</i>
<i>who planned all of this.</i>

17
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:40,707
<i>Manuel is Napoleon's</i>
<i>illegitimate half-brother.</i>

18
00:00:40,790 --> 00:00:44,544
They want you to take all the blame
for everything they have done.

19
00:00:44,627 --> 00:00:46,504
They're using you as their fall guy.

20
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:49,549
[Axl] <i>I'm sorry for holding you</i>
<i>hostage back then.</i>

21
00:00:49,632 --> 00:00:51,009
[Jamilah] <i>Shouldn't you be dead already?</i>

22
00:00:51,092 --> 00:00:52,510
<i>What happened? How are you still alive?</i>

23
00:00:52,594 --> 00:00:54,012
[Axl] <i>I don't know either.</i>

24
00:00:54,095 --> 00:00:56,306
<i>When I woke up, I was in a safe house.</i>

25
00:00:56,389 --> 00:00:59,017
<i>You work with Marcus Reyes' mother?</i>

26
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:03,271
[Axl] <i>Tell them</i>
<i>that the traitor in their ranks</i>

27
00:01:03,354 --> 00:01:06,524
is SPO4 Felix Domingo.

28
00:01:06,608 --> 00:01:08,651
General Carillo is planning something.

29
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:10,361
[Felix] <i>So just a little more…</i>

30
00:01:10,445 --> 00:01:13,990
<i>I can finally get my revenge</i>
<i>on Jalil Abubakar.</i>

31
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:16,242
[in English] Cuchy, baby girl!

32
00:01:16,326 --> 00:01:17,452
[Harold] <i>Cuchy!</i>

33
00:01:17,535 --> 00:01:21,623
Jalil, we are currently
in Ms. Maya May Kalaw's studio.

34
00:01:21,706 --> 00:01:22,916
What are you doing there?

35
00:01:22,999 --> 00:01:25,627
[Jamilah] <i>He wants to reveal</i>
<i>everything he knows.</i>

36
00:01:25,710 --> 00:01:28,880
<i>General Guerzon</i>
<i>was with Axl Rosales last night.</i>

37
00:01:28,963 --> 00:01:33,718
He wants me to tell you and Sir Marcus
that there is a traitor in your ranks.

38
00:01:33,802 --> 00:01:37,847
[Jamilah] <i>It's SPO4 Felix Domingo!</i>

39
00:01:38,348 --> 00:01:44,562
[tense music playing]

40
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:55,573
[mysterious theme music playing]

41
00:02:03,623 --> 00:02:06,668
[Maya, in English]
Massacre. School shooting.

42
00:02:06,751 --> 00:02:07,794
[in English] Foreign nationals

43
00:02:07,877 --> 00:02:11,256
being held hostage
and then killed en masse.

44
00:02:11,339 --> 00:02:14,092
[in English] <i>Assassination</i>
<i>of a top government official.</i>

45
00:02:14,175 --> 00:02:17,053
<i>These are just some of the cases</i>
<i>related to gun violence</i>

46
00:02:17,137 --> 00:02:19,264
<i>we are experiencing nowadays.</i>

47
00:02:19,347 --> 00:02:22,517
[in English] <i>And this problem</i>
<i>has reached a critical level.</i>

48
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,476
[Maya] <i>Tonight,</i>

49
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:27,188
we'll get to talk to someone
who always get mentioned

50
00:02:27,272 --> 00:02:29,357
ever since this problem started.

51
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:32,861
[in English] His arrest led
to the massacre at Isla Damai.

52
00:02:32,944 --> 00:02:36,739
[in English] He was kidnapped,
rescued, his name cleared.

53
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:38,408
[Maya] <i>But as of last night,</i>

54
00:02:38,491 --> 00:02:42,871
<i>he was being implicated once again</i>
<i>by General Manuel Carillo</i>

55
00:02:42,954 --> 00:02:47,167
<i>in the alleged bombing</i>
<i>of the M/V Doña Emilia</i>

56
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:49,627
<i>almost 30 years ago.</i>

57
00:02:49,711 --> 00:02:55,967
[suspenseful music playing]

58
00:03:02,974 --> 00:03:06,477
[in English] Please welcome
Datu Rahman Abubakar.

59
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:07,395
‪[inaudible]

60
00:03:19,908 --> 00:03:21,659
[Datu Rahman grunts]

61
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:25,413
[Datu Rahman groans]

62
00:03:25,914 --> 00:03:30,418
[tense music playing]

63
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:39,177
‪[music intensifies]

64
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:51,397
[Maya] Datu Rahman.

65
00:03:51,981 --> 00:03:57,612
What's your reaction to General Carillo's
statement against you?

66
00:03:57,695 --> 00:03:58,988
Jamilah.

67
00:03:59,739 --> 00:04:00,865
Jalil.

68
00:04:03,493 --> 00:04:04,327
‪[dramatic sting]

69
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:06,454
‪[dramatic sting]

70
00:04:08,873 --> 00:04:10,208
I'll admit it…

71
00:04:11,834 --> 00:04:13,378
when I was younger,

72
00:04:13,461 --> 00:04:15,880
I was involved with a syndicate.

73
00:04:19,676 --> 00:04:21,636
I won't deny that.

74
00:04:24,013 --> 00:04:27,100
But what General Carillo is saying,

75
00:04:27,183 --> 00:04:28,559
about the bombing

76
00:04:30,311 --> 00:04:32,647
of the M/V Doña Emilia…

77
00:04:36,567 --> 00:04:38,403
and the Japanese tour bus…

78
00:04:40,697 --> 00:04:42,532
I had nothing to do with those.

79
00:04:42,615 --> 00:04:47,537
[dramatic sting]

80
00:04:50,873 --> 00:04:54,419
General Carillo said
your son, Jalil Abubakar,

81
00:04:54,502 --> 00:04:56,713
is also involved with the syndicate.

82
00:04:56,796 --> 00:04:59,173
- [Maya] Is that true?
- [Datu Rahman] No!

83
00:05:00,466 --> 00:05:03,261
Jalil has nothing to do with this.

84
00:05:05,221 --> 00:05:08,891
[Datu Rahman] Don't drag my son
into the crimes I committed.

85
00:05:09,851 --> 00:05:12,228
<i>I left that life behind</i>

86
00:05:12,312 --> 00:05:15,523
<i>before Jalil ever came into my life!</i>

87
00:05:18,526 --> 00:05:21,904
[ominous music playing]

88
00:05:22,572 --> 00:05:27,076
Everything General Carillo's saying
is a lie.

89
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:29,370
He's framing me!

90
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:34,167
He wants to put all the blame on me.

91
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:39,005
[ominous music continues]

92
00:05:39,088 --> 00:05:40,590
Because the truth is…

93
00:05:42,508 --> 00:05:45,636
General Manuel Carillo…

94
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:51,559
is the mastermind behind
everything that's happening.

95
00:05:52,643 --> 00:05:54,854
Damn it!

96
00:05:54,937 --> 00:06:00,193
[dramatic stinging]

97
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:03,029
‪[dramatic sting]

98
00:06:03,446 --> 00:06:04,280
‪[dramatic sting]

99
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:06,574
‪[dramatic sting]

100
00:06:07,658 --> 00:06:08,493
‪[dramatic sting]

101
00:06:15,917 --> 00:06:20,546
[Datu Rahman] He's carrying on
what his brother,

102
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:23,549
Colonel Napoleon Marcelino, started.

103
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:25,551
He was the former leader

104
00:06:26,594 --> 00:06:27,720
of the syndicate!

105
00:06:27,804 --> 00:06:29,430
[gunshot]

106
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:35,895
[overlapping clamor]

107
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:43,569
- [tense music playing]
- [dramatic stinging]

108
00:07:19,772 --> 00:07:25,361
[inaudible]

109
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:36,998
- [Jamilah sobbing]
- Jamilah.

110
00:07:37,081 --> 00:07:40,209
- Ja-- Jamilah.
- Father!

111
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:41,335
- [Jamilah sobbing]
- [Datu Rahman gasps]

112
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:45,756
- Father!
- [Datu Rahman] Jalil.

113
00:07:46,591 --> 00:07:47,884
- Jalil.
- [Jamilah sobbing]

114
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:51,929
- Father! Father!
- Father… Father!

115
00:07:52,013 --> 00:07:53,598
- Father!
- [Jamilah] Father!

116
00:07:53,681 --> 00:07:57,810
- [wailing]
- [dramatic stinging]

117
00:08:01,522 --> 00:08:04,984
- Father! Father!
- Father!

118
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:08,738
- [Jamilah sobs]
- Call for help, hurry! Father!

119
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:12,366
- [Jamilah] <i>Father! Father!</i>
- [Jalil] <i>Father! Father!</i>

120
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:15,786
Jalil… [sobbing]

121
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:17,872
[Jamilah sobs]

122
00:08:18,456 --> 00:08:21,209
Father! Father!

123
00:08:22,668 --> 00:08:24,212
[Jalil] <i>Get help!</i>

124
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,589
[Jamilah sobbing]

125
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:29,217
[Jalil] No. Father, no.

126
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:34,555
Help us!

127
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:36,265
- [Jalil] Help!
- [Jamilah sobs]

128
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:39,060
[Jalil] Father! Father!

129
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:50,238
[stirring music playing]

130
00:08:50,321 --> 00:08:51,989
There! The man in the blue jacket!

131
00:08:57,161 --> 00:08:58,538
Hurry!

132
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:01,165
Hurry up!

133
00:09:11,259 --> 00:09:12,593
- [Teresa] What's your name?
- [Jalil groans]

134
00:09:13,177 --> 00:09:14,845
Can you hear me?

135
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:16,722
[weakly] Jalil…

136
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:21,060
[stirring music continues]

137
00:09:28,859 --> 00:09:30,236
Thank you.

138
00:09:30,319 --> 00:09:31,404
[heavy breathing]

139
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:33,656
Thank you…

140
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:34,865
so much.

141
00:09:37,535 --> 00:09:38,744
[Jalil] <i>Are you okay?</i>

142
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:39,996
[gasps]

143
00:09:40,079 --> 00:09:41,831
Are you hurt, Doc?

144
00:09:41,914 --> 00:09:47,545
[stirring music continues]

145
00:09:49,922 --> 00:09:54,719
Sometimes, I also think about my family.

146
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:57,221
My real family.

147
00:10:00,224 --> 00:10:01,726
Real family?

148
00:10:03,728 --> 00:10:05,354
I'm adopted, Doc.

149
00:10:10,359 --> 00:10:11,402
Thank you.

150
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:14,655
Be careful, son.

151
00:10:21,829 --> 00:10:22,997
Same to you.

152
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:29,045
[stirring music continues]

153
00:10:35,551 --> 00:10:37,053
[in English] Goddammit!

154
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:40,181
- What does this mean?!
- Espina…

155
00:10:42,099 --> 00:10:43,684
He's Jalil Abubakar.

156
00:10:47,605 --> 00:10:49,023
You mean to tell me…

157
00:10:49,899 --> 00:10:52,943
he's been spying on us in NLEA?

158
00:10:58,741 --> 00:10:59,742
[in English] Did you know?!

159
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:04,121
Did you know that Jalil Abubakar
pretended to be a cop?!

160
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:09,835
[stirring music playing]

161
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:12,421
We don't know anything about that, sir.

162
00:11:13,297 --> 00:11:18,135
[in English] Reyes, I want that criminal
arrested right now!

163
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:20,304
- Sir…
- What?

164
00:11:20,388 --> 00:11:22,056
Is there a problem?!

165
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:27,103
[sighs] Sir.

166
00:11:27,186 --> 00:11:28,020
[Azuelo] Reyes.

167
00:11:35,236 --> 00:11:36,487
No, sir.

168
00:11:37,655 --> 00:11:39,198
I'll handle Espina.

169
00:11:41,492 --> 00:11:43,202
I mean, Jalil Abubakar.

170
00:11:46,205 --> 00:11:47,039
[exhales]

171
00:11:47,123 --> 00:11:49,291
- [in English] Sabdani, go!
- [in English] Yes, sir.

172
00:11:58,092 --> 00:11:58,968
What?

173
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:03,222
You knew that Espina is Jalil Abubakar?

174
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:04,765
Yes, brother.

175
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:07,810
- He worked for Sir Mustapha.
- [pants]

176
00:12:08,310 --> 00:12:11,939
Why did Sir Mustapha
plant a spy in NLEA? [exhales]

177
00:12:12,022 --> 00:12:15,818
Because they're looking
for the real traitor in NLEA.

178
00:12:15,901 --> 00:12:19,238
- At the time, Sir Mustapha did not know
- [pants]

179
00:12:19,321 --> 00:12:21,490
that General Carillo
is the real mastermind.

180
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:23,409
[breathing deeply]

181
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:24,577
Brother…

182
00:12:26,495 --> 00:12:28,622
How did you manage to keep this
a secret from me?

183
00:12:28,706 --> 00:12:31,041
[breathes deeply] I'm sorry, brother.

184
00:12:31,542 --> 00:12:33,043
I badly wanted to tell you.

185
00:12:33,127 --> 00:12:35,629
But Sir Mustapha gave strict orders

186
00:12:36,213 --> 00:12:37,715
that I don't tell this to anyone else.

187
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:42,011
But look. Look.

188
00:12:42,511 --> 00:12:43,554
He was murdered.

189
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:48,851
How can I help you if you're hiding
this kind of information from me?

190
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:51,937
Jalil didn't want you to know.
He wants to protect you.

191
00:12:52,813 --> 00:12:54,273
And he didn't want you to get dragged

192
00:12:54,356 --> 00:12:56,734
once his real identity is revealed.

193
00:12:56,817 --> 00:13:00,237
He wants you to stay clean,
so you can continue the mission.

194
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:11,665
[breathing deeply]

195
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:14,210
We can't do anything about that now.

196
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:18,714
It's our duty to arrest him, brother.

197
00:13:21,133 --> 00:13:23,928
- [Jalil] Father!
- [Teresa] Allan! Allan! Allan.

198
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:26,180
- [Jalil] Father!
- [Teresa] Jamilah!

199
00:13:26,263 --> 00:13:27,723
[Jalil] Hurry!

200
00:13:28,682 --> 00:13:30,684
- [Jalil] Father.
- [Jamilah whimpers]

201
00:13:30,768 --> 00:13:32,019
[Jalil] Hurry!

202
00:13:33,687 --> 00:13:35,814
[Jamilah crying]

203
00:13:35,898 --> 00:13:37,733
[Jamilah] Father…

204
00:13:37,816 --> 00:13:43,489
[tense music playing]

205
00:13:43,572 --> 00:13:45,908
[Jalil] Father. Hurry up! Hurry!

206
00:13:48,619 --> 00:13:51,038
- [Jamilah] Hurry up!
- [man grunts]

207
00:13:51,121 --> 00:13:54,208
- [Teresa] Double IV, faster! Hurry!
- [groaning]

208
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:57,920
- [Jalil breathing heavily]
- [Jamilah whimpering]

209
00:13:58,003 --> 00:14:00,005
[Jamilah] Father. Father.

210
00:14:00,089 --> 00:14:01,173
[Jamilah whimpering]

211
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:09,306
[Jamilah whimpering, sobbing]

212
00:14:12,726 --> 00:14:15,020
[Jamilah crying]

213
00:14:15,104 --> 00:14:17,606
- [in English] Time of death, 12:34.
- [Jamilah screams]

214
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:19,024
Father!

215
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:25,447
[Jamilah wailing]

216
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:28,450
<i>Father! Father!</i>

217
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:31,078
<i>Father!</i>

218
00:14:32,413 --> 00:14:34,540
<i>Father!</i>

219
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,793
<i>Father!</i>

220
00:14:39,169 --> 00:14:45,134
[Jamilah sobbing]

221
00:14:48,387 --> 00:14:51,724
[voice breaking] <i>Father… Father…</i>

222
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:56,854
[Jamilah] <i>Father…</i>

223
00:14:56,937 --> 00:14:59,607
[Jalil gasping tearfully, in Arabic]
<i>God is great…</i>

224
00:14:59,690 --> 00:15:01,817
[yells, in Arabic] <i>God is great!</i>

225
00:15:02,818 --> 00:15:05,237
[in Arabic] <i>God is great!</i>

226
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:12,453
[Jalil] <i>Father!</i>

227
00:15:14,455 --> 00:15:17,333
<i>Father…</i>

228
00:15:19,293 --> 00:15:22,046
<i>Father!</i>

229
00:15:22,129 --> 00:15:23,923
[in Arabic] <i>God is great…</i>

230
00:15:24,715 --> 00:15:28,260
[Jalil, in Arabic] <i>God is great!</i>

231
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:32,890
[emotional music playing]

232
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:44,151
[Jamilah whimpering, crying]

233
00:15:44,234 --> 00:15:48,572
- [Jalil breathing heavily]
- [Jamilah crying]

234
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:55,120
- Bro.
- [Jamilah crying]

235
00:15:58,707 --> 00:16:01,919
- I'm sorry, bro.
- [Jamilah crying]

236
00:16:02,002 --> 00:16:03,295
[gasps]

237
00:16:05,547 --> 00:16:07,341
We're under orders to arrest you.

238
00:16:07,424 --> 00:16:08,884
[Jamilah] Father…

239
00:16:10,427 --> 00:16:15,057
[Jamilah sobs]

240
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:16,308
[Jamilah] Father…

241
00:16:20,354 --> 00:16:26,860
[Jamilah crying]

242
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:35,119
[Jamilah crying]

243
00:16:35,202 --> 00:16:36,036
[Jalil] Bro…

244
00:16:36,829 --> 00:16:38,664
Bro, please, grant me this.

245
00:16:39,289 --> 00:16:42,167
[Jamilah whimpering]

246
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:44,628
I have to bury my father.

247
00:16:44,712 --> 00:16:47,381
Bro, I have to bury my father.

248
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:49,883
I'm sorry, bro.

249
00:16:51,093 --> 00:16:56,724
- [emotional music continues]
- [sobs]

250
00:16:56,807 --> 00:16:57,975
[Jamilah crying]

251
00:16:58,058 --> 00:16:59,226
Bro!

252
00:17:00,310 --> 00:17:02,187
- [Jamilah crying]
- [Jalil] Bro.

253
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:05,399
Father…

254
00:17:06,191 --> 00:17:09,862
[Jamilah whimpering]

255
00:17:09,945 --> 00:17:10,988
[Jalil exhales deeply]

256
00:17:12,823 --> 00:17:14,658
[Jalil, in Arabic] God is great…

257
00:17:14,742 --> 00:17:16,201
[Jamilah] Father…

258
00:17:16,285 --> 00:17:19,538
[in Arabic] God is great. Father!

259
00:17:21,623 --> 00:17:23,208
[Jalil] Father…

260
00:17:24,752 --> 00:17:26,128
[Jalil] <i>Father…</i>

261
00:17:26,211 --> 00:17:32,551
[Jamilah sobbing]

262
00:17:32,634 --> 00:17:39,475
[Jalil, Jamilah sobbing]

263
00:17:46,940 --> 00:17:49,151
[Norhana sobs] Omar…

264
00:17:49,234 --> 00:17:52,321
[all sobbing]

265
00:17:52,404 --> 00:17:53,781
This means

266
00:17:53,864 --> 00:17:57,242
Jalil was the police officer
who arrested Datu Rahman.

267
00:18:01,205 --> 00:18:05,375
[emotional music continues]

268
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:07,920
Datu Rahman is gone.

269
00:18:08,003 --> 00:18:09,797
They killed him.

270
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:11,924
- [sobs] They killed him.
- [Norhana] Omar…

271
00:18:12,007 --> 00:18:14,051
Omar… Omar, w-what will happen--

272
00:18:14,134 --> 00:18:18,388
What will happen now
to Jalil and Jamilah, Omar?

273
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:21,391
Datu Rahman is dead, Omar.

274
00:18:21,475 --> 00:18:23,393
[Norhana sobbing]

275
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:25,395
Allah will watch over them.

276
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:30,484
[Norhana] Datu Rahman
is no longer with us, Omar.

277
00:18:30,567 --> 00:18:35,197
[sobbing continues]

278
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:38,992
It has been verified by Major Espina--

279
00:18:39,076 --> 00:18:41,161
[tense music playing]

280
00:18:41,245 --> 00:18:46,750
Jalil Abubakar… that Domingo is among

281
00:18:46,834 --> 00:18:50,212
the traitors in our ranks!

282
00:18:50,295 --> 00:18:52,464
That bastard…

283
00:18:52,548 --> 00:18:57,344
And that he was
the shooter of Datu Rahman

284
00:18:57,427 --> 00:19:01,098
while Maya Mae Kalaw
was interviewing him on live TV!

285
00:19:03,183 --> 00:19:04,768
The mission before you

286
00:19:04,852 --> 00:19:09,857
is to arrest SPO4 Felix Domingo!

287
00:19:10,774 --> 00:19:11,817
[in English] Understood?!

288
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,527
- [in English] Sir, yes, sir!
- [in English] Sir, yes, sir!

289
00:19:15,112 --> 00:19:17,614
[in English] What the hell is happening?!

290
00:19:17,698 --> 00:19:19,950
Why hasn't Jalil Abubakar
been arrested yet?!

291
00:19:21,034 --> 00:19:22,286
Are you capable of handling this,

292
00:19:22,369 --> 00:19:25,330
or must I call on other officers
to do your job?!

293
00:19:25,914 --> 00:19:27,875
Gen. Villanueva, sir.

294
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:32,880
Jalil Abubakar is already
in Agent Reyes's custody.

295
00:19:32,963 --> 00:19:35,841
They're only waiting
for Datu Rahman's autopsy

296
00:19:35,924 --> 00:19:36,967
to be completed.

297
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:40,304
Also, Jalil Abubakar
had only one last request.

298
00:19:40,387 --> 00:19:43,807
To bury his own father.

299
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:45,434
[in English] And I allowed it.

300
00:19:45,517 --> 00:19:49,313
Since when do criminals have the right

301
00:19:49,396 --> 00:19:51,607
- to demand special treatment?!
- [slams table]

302
00:19:51,690 --> 00:19:54,568
[tense music continues]

303
00:19:55,235 --> 00:19:56,278
[in English] Sir.

304
00:19:56,361 --> 00:19:58,113
We have good intel

305
00:19:58,197 --> 00:20:01,658
that Jalil Abubakar
was an asset of Sir Mustapha

306
00:20:01,742 --> 00:20:03,952
and that he was the one
who brought him into our ranks!

307
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:05,329
Yeah?

308
00:20:05,412 --> 00:20:07,372
But where is Mustapha now?

309
00:20:08,373 --> 00:20:10,792
How can we verify that

310
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:13,420
if the person is already dead?!

311
00:20:13,503 --> 00:20:14,838
[in English] Sir.

312
00:20:14,922 --> 00:20:19,009
If I made the wrong decision,
I'll take full responsibility.

313
00:20:19,885 --> 00:20:21,762
But for now, sir,

314
00:20:21,845 --> 00:20:26,266
let us pay our respects to the dead.

315
00:20:27,017 --> 00:20:33,065
Allow a son to bury his father
according to Muslim tradition.

316
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:41,657
[music becomes gloomy]

317
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:45,035
[door clicks open, slams shut]

318
00:20:45,118 --> 00:20:46,245
[Azuelo sighs]

319
00:20:47,412 --> 00:20:48,747
[in English] Goddammit!

320
00:20:50,165 --> 00:20:51,458
Sir, still a good job.

321
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:54,419
- [exhales deeply]
- [slams table]

322
00:20:59,132 --> 00:21:01,260
What are you waiting for?!

323
00:21:01,343 --> 00:21:05,013
[in English] Go and arrest
SPO4 Felix Domingo!

324
00:21:05,097 --> 00:21:07,015
[in English] Now! Move!

325
00:21:07,766 --> 00:21:09,559
[door clicks open]

326
00:21:11,895 --> 00:21:13,105
[door clicks shut]

327
00:21:17,651 --> 00:21:19,361
[somber music playing]

328
00:21:19,444 --> 00:21:23,323
[Jalil breathing deeply]

329
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:27,661
[sighs]

330
00:21:40,465 --> 00:21:42,467
I'd understand if you're mad with me.

331
00:21:46,388 --> 00:21:48,598
I'm sorry for keeping a secret from you.

332
00:21:57,024 --> 00:21:59,192
Usman told me that

333
00:22:00,819 --> 00:22:03,697
this was your mission from Sir Mustapha.

334
00:22:07,576 --> 00:22:11,163
[Jalil] At first, all I wanted
was to bring back my father and to…

335
00:22:11,246 --> 00:22:13,123
[sniffles lightly]

336
00:22:13,206 --> 00:22:16,335
…give justice to my neighbors
who lost their lives.

337
00:22:17,711 --> 00:22:20,756
But then I witnessed how bad
the situation truly is.

338
00:22:21,298 --> 00:22:23,633
How deep and…

339
00:22:24,593 --> 00:22:27,637
far-reaching their influence
is within the police force

340
00:22:27,721 --> 00:22:29,473
and the government.

341
00:22:33,143 --> 00:22:36,521
It makes sense now that you
chose not to disappear

342
00:22:37,439 --> 00:22:40,400
after you and Datu Rahman
were proven innocent.

343
00:22:44,738 --> 00:22:45,947
[sniffles]

344
00:22:47,115 --> 00:22:48,450
When Sir Mustapha died,

345
00:22:48,533 --> 00:22:52,245
I knew my identity was at risk
of being exposed.

346
00:22:53,205 --> 00:22:55,957
But I had to finish
the mission he left behind.

347
00:22:59,336 --> 00:23:03,882
I had to help you find
and arrest General Carillo.

348
00:23:13,016 --> 00:23:14,559
Espina…

349
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:16,937
Espina…

350
00:23:20,357 --> 00:23:23,318
Police Major Allan Espina is not real.

351
00:23:26,571 --> 00:23:28,782
But everything I showed you…

352
00:23:32,911 --> 00:23:34,704
All of it was real.

353
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:40,335
I didn't just see you as a friend.

354
00:23:44,047 --> 00:23:45,674
I came to see you as my brother.

355
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:01,565
[tense music playing]

356
00:24:01,648 --> 00:24:02,566
[Azuelo] <i>Find him!</i>

357
00:24:02,649 --> 00:24:07,696
<i>And don't stop until you capture</i>
<i>the traitor Domingo!</i>

358
00:24:08,405 --> 00:24:10,991
Our plan isn't finished yet.

359
00:24:11,575 --> 00:24:13,702
[Marcus] <i>You have the right</i>
<i>to remain silent.</i>

360
00:24:13,785 --> 00:24:15,912
<i>Anything you say can</i>
<i>and will be used against you</i>

361
00:24:15,996 --> 00:24:17,622
<i>in any Philippine court.</i>

362
00:24:17,706 --> 00:24:19,457
[Jamilah sobs] <i>Brother Jalil…</i>

363
00:24:20,584 --> 00:24:22,711
<i>Take care of yourself.</i>

364
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:28,842
<i>I'm sorry, I had to protect</i>
<i>my brother's identity.</i> [sobs]

365
00:24:28,925 --> 00:24:31,803
But there's no need to get a DNA test now.

366
00:24:32,929 --> 00:24:34,639
Those two are the real criminals,

367
00:24:34,723 --> 00:24:36,349
and yet you call me the traitor?!

368
00:24:36,433 --> 00:24:38,435
- [Felix] <i>How dare you!</i>
- [man] <i>You bastard!</i>

369
00:24:38,518 --> 00:24:40,187
[overlapping shouting]

370
00:24:40,812 --> 00:24:42,522
Can you really protect me?

371
00:24:42,606 --> 00:24:43,773
[in English] With my life, madam.

372
00:24:46,985 --> 00:24:48,069
[gunshots]

373
00:24:48,153 --> 00:24:49,821
[Nathalia] <i>Who is your master?!</i>

374
00:24:49,905 --> 00:24:51,031
[Nathalia gasps]

375
00:24:51,114 --> 00:24:52,199
[Jalil] <i>What's going on?</i>

376
00:24:52,824 --> 00:24:55,243
Jalil, let's go!
They're going to kill you!
